      },
      "level": {
        "value": 10
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role (B6a):</strong> the alchemical death-gas the orc besiegers pumped through the arrow slits to kill Mandraivus's archers — soaked five centuries in the curse until it <em>woke</em>. The harmless yellow wisps curling through both defense corridors are its camouflage; the six sword-clutching corpses in B6a are its juju-zombie puppets. All stay quiescent until someone enters B6a — then the mist wells up among the dead and engulfs. <strong>Once roused, it and its zombies pursue foes throughout the entire castle.</strong></p>",
